timeline.summary: This document is an email return concurrence form (ED-1036 Rev. 10-16-2009) related to a death investigation, Case ID #: 90A-NY-3151227. The email concerns Jeffrey Epstein as a victim and was drafted on 09/05/2019. It was approved by SSA and marked as UNSUB(S).

The form was drafted on 2025-12-27 and references an OIG referral (CIA-2019-05324) received on 10-16-2009, categorized as “Other.” The case ID is 90A-NY-3151227, noting Epstein as a victim and the investigation’s focus. It includes a facial record dated 09/23/2019.

The record includes phone records for MCC Caller Station 6317, provided by the Office of Inspector General (OIG) on October 16, 2009. The case ID is 90A-NY-3151227, involving Jeffrey Epstein as a victim and classified as an UNSUB(S) death investigation.

The FBI case file, EFTA00005716, pertains to Case ID #31E-MM-108062, involving Jeffrey Epstein. The case was drafted on November 25, 2010, and initially handled by the Jacksonville Field Office, Squad 10, with contact occurring in Jacksonville, Florida.  On November 26, 2010, the case was transferred to the Miami Division.  Source information received to date is redacted.

The FBI case file, EFTA00005717, pertains to a case investigated by the Jacksonville Field Office (Squad 10), Case ID #31E-MM-108062, involving Jeffrey Epstein. The initial report was drafted on 11/25/2010 and forwarded to the Miami Division on 11/26/2010. A contact occurred on 2010-11-12 in Jacksonville, Florida. The source reporting received information to date.

This document is a routine advisory regarding travel approval for FBI agents to Sydney, Australia, from March 14, 2011, to March 21, 2011, to interview Jeffrey Epstein and Ghislaine Maxwell in connection with a child prostitution investigation (WSTA). The Criminal Investigative Crimes Against Children Unit (CACU) approved the Miami Division’s request.  The advisory outlines specific procedures including: submitting an Electronic Clearance (EC) to the Legat office in Canberra, Australia; completing an Electronic Country Clearance (eCC) through the Department of State; and submitting a Clearance Passage Worksheet.  All submissions must be unclassified except for sensitive information which should be handled securely. Coordination with the Legat office and the Office of International Operations (OIO) is critical for securing Country Clearances.

This document is an official record from the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) dated June 16, 2011, pertaining to “Documentation of Services.” Case ID # is NY-302571. The document is classified as UNCLASSIFIED.

This document is a forwarded email chain concerning an “AOT Team 4 Meeting” held on August 20, 2018, at Room 3256. The email originated from an FBI agent ([REDACTED]) and was sent to another recipient ([REDACTED]). The email includes the reference number EFTA00037276 and is marked as “UNCLASSIFIED.”

An event, titled “AOT Team 4 Meeting – UNCLASSIFIED,” took place on August 22, 2018, from 17:00 to 18:00 in Room 3256. The event was organized with a priority of 5 and included a reminder displayed 15 minutes prior to the start. Attendees included [REDACTED] and [REDACTED]. Related documents EFTA00037278 also exists.

A FOIA request (1424728) regarding Jeffrey Epstein is being processed. The request was initiated by Bill Stevens. The file number associated with the request is 31E-MM-108062. RIDS is requesting information from the CDC and a SA regarding the status of the ongoing investigation, potential impact on the investigation if information is disclosed, whether releasable material exists, and whether the subject, Jeffrey Epstein, has been interviewed. The FBI Vault contains serials 1-250 of the investigative file, which were released from Civil Action 17-CV-03956, and a consultation was conducted with an expert regarding releasing serials 251-257. A response is required within 7 days.

This document is a communication (email) regarding a redacted file named “EFTA00030110.pdf,” which contains information related to Jeffrey Epstein. The email was sent on January 25, 2019, and includes attached documents, including a PDF and a message, both labeled “UNCLASSIFIED.” The email also references a pending FOIA request.

This document is an email sent from the FBI’s dropbox®ic.fbi.gov account to an unknown recipient on January 25, 2019. The email, titled “FBINET to UNET Uploaded Files,” includes an attachment named “FW_Pending_FOIA_1424728_-_JEFFREY_EPSTEIN_-_UNCLASSIFIED.msg,” related to EFTA00037894.

A FOIA request (Case #1424728) regarding Jeffrey Epstein is being processed. The request was submitted by Bill Stevens. The relevant file number is 31E-NY-3027571. RIDS is conducting a redaction analysis to determine responsive information and appropriate exemptions for release. Standard questions are being posed to assess the investigation's status, potential impact on ongoing investigations, and whether releasable material exists. The request is due January 31, 2019.

This document concerns the receipt of the Correctional Services Manual (EFTA00036418.pdf) for staff at the Federal Bureau of Prisons, MCC New York. The manual provides information on institution security procedures and is intended for law enforcement use. Distribution is controlled and restricted to Bureau components with a sensitive but unclassified status. Staff must maintain the manual in a secure location, and any loss requires immediate notification to regional administrators.

This email chain discusses the status of video footage related to EFTA00029280, specifically concerning DVR1 and DVR2.  The primary focus is on recovering footage from DVR2, which experienced a system failure and ceased recording before July 29th. Data recovery efforts are considered a long-term, uncertain project potentially requiring 6+ months. DVR1 footage was partially exported.  Questions are raised regarding hard drive size needs for SHU footage, the total number of cameras available, and the accuracy of camera location lists.  A request for an EC (Expedite Capability) is suggested if OTD/DFAS/DFAU wishes to proceed with further recovery efforts. The communication involves multiple individuals and classifications of UNCLASSIFIED//FOUO.

The report is classified as UNCLASSIFIED and designates the case as UNSUB(S).

An email exchange discusses a reported Epstein victim claim received by a Special Agent with the Diplomatic Security Service (DSS) – New York Field Office. The email is marked as UNCLASSIFIED.

This document is an Intake Screening Phone Log related to a death investigation, Case ID 90A-NY-3151227, involving Jeffrey Epstein as a victim. The log was provided by the OIG Special Agent on 11/3/2020 and dated 03/04/2021. It is associated with the EFTA00035758 file.

This is an FBI document, Case ID # EFTA00025005, concerning the case of Jeffrey Epstein and a child sex trafficking investigation. It details outreach support efforts following an OPR briefing on findings dated November 11, 2020. An updated contact information list as of November 18, 2020 is included as an enclosure.

The document appears to be a record of ongoing efforts to review evidence related to the Epstein investigation. It primarily involves individuals assisting a “SA” (likely a Special Assistant or similar role) with evidence redaction, conversion of media files, and binder reviews. Multiple individuals, identified by redacted email addresses and case identifiers (EFTA000149xx), are involved in these tasks. The work includes assisting with photo scrubbing, evidence review in CAIR, and converting DVD evidence to a reviewable system. The document spans from November 2019 to December 2020, with a significant focus on redacting images and assisting with the Maxwell investigation. The classification level is consistently UNCLASSIFIED//FOUO.

This is the FD-794 Payment Request form, version 2.0, revised as of March 11, 2021. It is used by the FBI to request and process payments for authorized expenses, including advance payments and reimbursements. The form collects information such as Social Security Number, case details (case number, date, justification), and employee information. It outlines authorized uses of the data, emphasizes mandatory disclosure, and specifies maintenance within the FBI Central Records System. The form includes sections for approval by various FBI personnel and for finance office settlement of the payment, detailing methods of payment (e.g., cash receipt, OTCnet). Specifically, this form details a request for reimbursement of meals for trial witnesses incurred on 06/12/2021, under case number I50D-NY-3027571.

This is form FD-794, a Payment Request submitted by the FBI. It requests funds for reimbursement of expenses, specifically meals for trial witnesses, incurred by the C-20 unit (E-NY-302757) on 06/23/21. The request is authorized by FBI regulations and E.O. 9397 and 13478. Information collected includes employee details, case information, and justification for the expense. The form includes sections for finance office completion and approval by various FBI supervisory and finance personnel. The overall classification is Unclassified.

This document is an unofficial FBI import form, Case ID #90A-NY-3151227, related to a death investigation involving Jeffrey Epstein. This document is an FBI Miami internal form, the “Complaint Form FD-71,” used for recording complaints. It includes sections for identifying the subject of the complaint (name, aliases, demographic information), detailing the facts of the complaint, and assessing the level of sensitivity. The form is designed for internal use within the FBI and outlines various locations and divisions within the FBI network, including specific field offices and research facilities. It also includes a classification level selection (Unclassified, Sensitive, Confidential).

The document, EFTA00015037.pdf, presents a list of individuals with associated data. The data includes: *   Name *   Date of Birth (DOB) *   Source of information *   Multiple entries include individuals such as NYPD personnel (various years), Jeffrey Epstein, and Ghislaine Maxwell, along with dates of birth and source information (e.g., US PP/2003). The document appears to be a redaction analysis record, with each page numbered and identified with an EFTA code. The content is marked as UNCLASSIFIED//FOUO or UNCLASSIFIED//FOU0.
